Class ResearchGameModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • ResearchGameModel

  • public class ResearchGameModel
extends java.lang.Object

    ResearchGameModel Class

    Going by the MVC design pattern, this is the Model class. This is more or less the brain of the ResearchGame. Everything that is needs to be updated is calcualted here and sent over to the view to paint. This class is fed by the controller, with each key press of the game controls the players direction is updated in conrtoller and sent here to this class to do the game logic. The main methods are multiple collision detections like player with crabs and player with out-of-bounds, and the update location which updates the position of everything that moves and sent to View.

      • ResearchGameModel

        public ResearchGameModel(int width,
                         int height,
                         int imageWidth,
                         int imageHeight,
                         java.lang.Boolean tutorial)

        ResearcherGameModel Constructor

        Constructs the Model. Takes in a width, height, imageWidth, and imageHeight from the views knowledge of screen size and image (sprite) size. Outside of this is creates crabs and adds them to the crabs array and creates rectangles for boundaries and add those to the rectangle array, both with specific placement
        Parameters:
        width - width of the frame, passed in from View
        height - height of the frame, passed in from the View
        imageWidth - width of the images
        imageHeight - height of the images

        public void crabCollisionChecker()

        crabCollisionChecker

        Checks if the any of the crab's rectanclges from any crab on the list is intersecting the players rectangle. If so, then subtract a life point from player if the crab has not been steppedOn before, and set that crabs steppedOn to be true
